 cut in pieces (3 cm)","200 g cooked, peeled prawns","20 g light soy sauce","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","1 spring onion, finely chopped, for garnishing","2 Tbsp dried onion flakes, for garnishing","½ cucumber, halved lengthways then thinly sliced, for serving","2 tomatoes, cut in wedges, for serving","sriracha sauce, to taste (optional)"]}],"id":"r423879","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Tl8b1XQYfGo\/XZMzicMlPdI\/AAAAAAAAayc\/eQXIxqvI_-4fAcW2jGHz8cWrS93dT3SvwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_eBvyfbyJrRFDhOW4.png","title":"Barley Nasi Goreng with Prawns","publishedAt":"2019-03-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"22 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"52 g","calories":"1750 kJ \/ 416 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, aluminium foil","hintsAndTricks":["Whilst brown rice has more fibre than white rice, its GI is only slightly lower, both with a GI of <b>around 50.<b> This recipe substitutes the rice traditionally used in Nasi Goreng with pearl barley, which has much more fibre than white rice and has a GI approx. half that of rice.","In <b>step 2,<b> before placing Varoma into position, check the liquid in the barley. The starch can make the liquid become quite thick. If this happens, add <b>100-200 g<b> boiling water before steaming the eggs.","In <b>step 5,<b> heating time will depend on the size of prawns used. <b>5 minutes<b> will be enough for small prawns. If using larger prawns, prolong time as necessary until prawns are heated thoroughly.","For a nicer presentation, transfer nasi goreng to a bowl then invert onto a serving plate."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","4 portions"]}